.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_UIDraggableItem
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The UI Draggable item will make any UI element draggable on the canvas.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: If a UI Draggable item is set to Restrict To Drop Zone = true then the UI Draggable item must be a child of an element that has the VRTK_UIDropZone script applied to it to ensure it starts in a valid drop zone.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/034_Controls_InteractingWithUnityUI demonstrates a collection of UI elements that are draggable

fields.name: validDropZone
fields.summary: The current valid drop zone the dragged element is hovering over.
